<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Gonzalo Higuain has been pictured with Inter Miami's managing owner Jorge Mas as he closes in on his move to the club.</p>

<p>Higuain has arrived in United States, with Juventus having terminated his contract a year early to allow him to secure the move.</p>

<p>Mas posted a picture on Twitter of himself and Higuain accompanied by the caption: 'A warm welcome to Gonzalo Higuain, a world class striker and champion.'</p>

<p>A warm welcome to Gonzalo Higuain, a world class striker and champion.⁦<?php echo e('@'); ?>G_Higuain⁩ pic.twitter.com/29wT86aA2J</p>

<p>Higuain had his contract at Juventus terminated a year early in order to allow him to leave</p>

<p>Higuain's brother Nicolas was in Italy on Tuesday to hold discussions over the former Argentina international's future.</p>

<p>Once his move to Inter Miami is finalised, the 32-year-old is poised to link up with his former Juventus team-mate Blaise Matuidi.</p>

<p>Higuain will join David Beckham's Inter Miami, where his ex-team-mate Blaise Matuidi plays</p>

<p>Inter Miami, owned by David Beckham, secured a 2-1 victory over Atlanta United this week.</p>

<p>Higuain scored 66 goals in 148 appearances for Juventus, winning three Serie A titles and two Coppa Italias. </p>

<p>During his time at Juventus he had spells on loan at AC Milan and Chelsea. </p>
